# 🌸 Iris Flower Classifier

This is my **first Machine Learning project** using Python and Scikit-learn.  
It predicts the type of Iris flower (**Setosa, Versicolor, Virginica**) based on petal and sepal measurements.  

---

## 📌 Project Overview
- Dataset: [Iris Dataset (built into scikit-learn)](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/datasets/plot_iris_dataset.html)  
- Algorithm: Random Forest Classifier  
- Tools: Python, Scikit-learn, Google Colab  

---

## ⚙️ How It Works
1. Load the Iris dataset.  
2. Split the data into training and testing sets.  
3. Train a Random Forest Classifier.  
4. Test the model and check accuracy.  
5. Predict flower species for new inputs.  

